<h2><strong>üì• How to Download Oracle VirtualBox</strong></h2>
<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 1. Visit the Official VirtualBox Website</strong></h3>
<p>Go to the official download page:</p>
<p>üëâ <strong>https://www.virtualbox.org</strong></p>

<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 2. Select ‚ÄúDownload VirtualBox‚Äù</strong></h3>
<p>On the homepage, click <strong>Download VirtualBox</strong> to open the downloads section.</p>

<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 3. Choose Your Operating System</strong></h3>
<p>Under <strong>VirtualBox Platform Packages</strong>, choose the installer for your system:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Windows hosts</strong> ‚Äì Windows 10/11</li>
    <li><strong>macOS hosts</strong> ‚Äì Mac devices</li>
    <li><strong>Linux distributions</strong> ‚Äì Ubuntu, Debian, etc.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example (Windows):</strong> Click <strong>Windows hosts</strong> to begin downloading.</p>

<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 4. Download the Installer</strong></h3>
<p>You will download a file similar to:</p>

<pre>
VirtualBox-7.x.x-Win.exe      <!-- Windows -->
VirtualBox-7.x.x-macOS.dmg    <!-- macOS -->
VirtualBox-7.x.x-Linux.run    <!-- Linux -->
</pre>

<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 5. Run the Installer</strong></h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Windows:</strong> Double-click the <code>.exe</code> file</li>
    <li><strong>macOS:</strong> Open the <code>.dmg</code> file and drag VirtualBox to Applications</li>
    <li><strong>Linux:</strong> Run the <code>.run</code> file using terminal with executable permissions</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3><strong>‚û°Ô∏è 6. Complete the Installation</strong></h3>
<p>Follow the installation wizard:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Click <strong>Next</strong> through the prompts</li>
    <li>Allow any permissions or drivers it requests</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Install</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Finish</strong> to launch VirtualBox</li>
</ol>

